#: instructor-training/_extras/guide.md:59
msgid "### Using Slides"
msgstr ""

#: instructor-training/_extras/guide.md:61
msgid ""
"Whether or not slides should be used be used during instructor training\n"
"is a subject of [frequent discussion][great-slide-issue]."
msgstr ""

#: instructor-training/_extras/guide.md:64
msgid ""
"The main **advantage** is that slides provide a visual aid when explaining\n"
"complex concepts or when presenting learning objectives and challenges.\n"
"The most notable **disadvantage** is that it can give the false impression\n"
"that it is okay to use slides rather than live coding in SWC/DC/LC workshops\n"
"For online instructor training events, there are two additional risks:\n"
"the slides may fail to advance using Zoom's screen share feature and\n"
"you risk losing the audience's attention because your face is less prominent."
msgstr ""

#: instructor-training/_extras/guide.md:72
msgid ""
"If you chose to use slides in your workshop,\n"
"this [Google Drive folder][slides-folder] contains slides with diagrams, cartoons, and text that trainers have used past workshops. Feel free to reuse the existing materials or add your own slides."
msgstr ""

