#: instructor-training/_extras/guide.md:131
msgid "## IV. Using Zoom  for Online Trainings"
msgstr ""

#: instructor-training/_extras/guide.md:133
msgid "<a name=\"zoom\"></a>"
msgstr ""

#: instructor-training/_extras/guide.md:135
msgid ""
"Online Carpentry Instructor Training events are held on [Zoom][zoom-home]. You can set up a personal Zoom\n"
"account for yourself for free. This personal account will be able to attend the training event\n"
"(or any other online Carpentry event), but will not be able to act as host.   "
msgstr ""

#: instructor-training/_extras/guide.md:139
msgid ""
"About a week before your event, you will be given login credentials for a Carpentry account.\n"
"This account will be the host for the event and will have extra privileges including the\n"
"ability to mute participants and assign participants into breakout rooms. Decide ahead of time with your co-Trainer(s) who will log-in with these credentials. The host\n"
"can transfer host privileges to other participants, so you will be able to trade host status\n"
"back and forth with your co-Trainers during the event.  "
msgstr ""

#: instructor-training/_extras/guide.md:145
msgid ""
"All Carpentry online events are set-up such that participants can enter the room without the\n"
"host being present. If you ever get an error message saying you can’t join the room because\n"
"you’re not the host, please contact Carpentry staff immediately.   "
msgstr ""

# header
#: instructor-training/_extras/guide.md:149
msgid "### Host abilities:  "
msgstr ""

# unordered list
#: instructor-training/_extras/guide.md:150
msgid ""
"- “Mute” is in the lower left. To mute other participants, the host can go "
"to “Manage Participants”, hover over a participant’s name, and click “mute”."
"  "
msgstr ""

# unordered list
#: instructor-training/_extras/guide.md:151
msgid ""
"- When the room host clicks “End Meeting”, a dialogue box appears with three"
" options: “Cancel”, “Leave Meeting” and “End Meeting for All”. Be careful "
"not to end the meeting if you are simply leaving the room temporarily while "
"your co-Trainer teaches.  "
msgstr ""

# unordered list
#: instructor-training/_extras/guide.md:152
msgid ""
"- Only the host has the ability to create “Breakout rooms”. The button for "
