"* From JS: \"What happens is that we send participants home at the end of "
"day one with a request to look up more about the Carpentries workshop types "
"and then we ask them what questions they have at the start of day two. While"
" the intent is that these questions will be put in the etherpad and then "
"taken up later in one way or another this doesn't happen or at least only "
"happens in part. The result is either a lot of saying, \"We'll cover that "
"this afternoon\" or pulling parts of the relevant afternoon sessions into "
