# unordered list
#: instructor-training/_extras/guide.md:207
msgid ""
"\t* Response from CK: I've never had the problem described by JS; people are"
" usually willing to wait (especially once we dive into live coding), and I "
"make sure to answer all questions (and take new ones!) in the afternoon."
msgstr ""

# unordered list
#: instructor-training/_extras/guide.md:208
msgid ""
"\t* Response from KW: Another option is to have people put questions into "
"the etherpad in the morning, and then answer them (in the etherpad) during "
"the live coding practice. Trainees can read them at any time then, and you "
"can refer back to them when necessary."
msgstr ""

